WEBVTT

1
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:46,260
Twenty questions. Go.

2
00:01:49,060 --> 00:01:51,460
You're a man. Are you in politics?

3
00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:58,060
Warm beer. Tastes like piss.

4
00:02:06,740 --> 00:02:08,460
It's your turn, babe.

5
00:02:08,940 --> 00:02:10,380
Dead or alive?

6
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:14,660
Don't you think that's
a really stupid question these days?

7
00:02:16,420 --> 00:02:18,300
You know, he's kind of an asshole,

8
00:02:18,340 --> 00:02:20,100
but if you need me
to take care of him, I will.

9
00:02:20,180 --> 00:02:21,140
I can hear you.

10
00:02:21,220 --> 00:02:23,780
He's the one in the family
with all the brains.

11
00:02:23,860 --> 00:02:25,300
Is that right?

12
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:34,740
All right, the interstate's coming up.
What do we do?

13
00:02:34,820 --> 00:02:37,100
Don't get on it. Stay on this back road.

14
00:02:37,180 --> 00:02:38,580
How come every time you say that,

15
00:02:38,660 --> 00:02:41,500
we end up in a three-hour scenic tour
in the middle of nowhere?

16
00:02:41,540 --> 00:02:43,060
Look, we agreed on the rules, didn't we?

17
00:02:43,140 --> 00:02:45,140
And by taking it, we're breaking what?

18
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:47,700
The rule that says
we shouldn't take the interstate.

19
00:02:47,780 --> 00:02:51,780
"I guess we wouldn't want
to break any rules," he said,

20
00:02:51,860 --> 00:02:54,180
drinking his beer
as he drove the stolen Mercedes

21
00:02:54,260 --> 00:02:57,780
ridiculously over the speed limit,
and, look, no hands!

22
00:02:57,900 --> 00:02:59,540
- Babe, don't!
- Stop!

23
00:03:00,380 --> 00:03:02,180
- Stop it, you moron!
- Don't!

24
00:03:09,020 --> 00:03:13,940
- All right, smartass, I'll read the map.
- Can you? It has actual writing on it.

25
00:03:14,940 --> 00:03:16,220
Very funny.

26
00:03:19,100 --> 00:03:20,740
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

27
00:03:29,060 --> 00:03:30,340
Hey, guys.

28
00:03:31,260 --> 00:03:33,420
All right, windows, everybody.

29
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:38,740
What the hell is this guy doing?

30
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:42,380
My daughter and I, we ran out of gas.

31
00:03:44,260 --> 00:03:47,100
All right, sir,
please move your car out of the road.

32
00:03:47,180 --> 00:03:51,340
We left Denver yesterday morning.
Last gas we got was Colorado Springs.

33
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:54,420
I'm sorry, we can't help you.
Now move your car!

34
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:55,980
Look, all we need
is just a little bit of gas.

35
00:03:56,060 --> 00:03:57,620
Yeah, I'm sure you do.
You and everybody else.

36
00:03:57,660 --> 00:03:59,340
Stay where you are!

37
00:03:59,420 --> 00:04:02,380
We can trade you for it.
We got food and water.

38
00:04:02,460 --> 00:04:05,340
- Brian, we have more than enough.
- More than... How do you know that?

39
00:04:05,420 --> 00:04:08,500
- I said do not get any closer!
- Brian, he looks clean.

40
00:04:08,580 --> 00:04:10,500
Or he could be incubating.
Think about it for a second...

41
00:04:10,580 --> 00:04:12,540
Guys! She's got it.

42
00:04:13,020 --> 00:04:14,060
Shit!

43
00:04:15,460 --> 00:04:17,580
Come on, come on, come on...

44
00:04:34,060 --> 00:04:35,860
They'll die out there.

45
00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:38,260
Everyone dies.

46
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:49,380
<i>The rules are simple.
At least, that's how my brother sees it.</i>

47
00:04:50,620 --> 00:04:53,540
<i>One, avoid the infected at all costs.</i>

48
00:04:53,980 --> 00:04:56,340
<i>Their breath is highly contagious.</i>

49
00:04:57,020 --> 00:05:00,980
<i>Two, disinfect anything they've touched
in the last 24 hours.</i>

50
00:05:01,780 --> 00:05:05,780
<i>Three, the sick are already dead.
They can't be saved.</i>

51
00:05:07,020 --> 00:05:08,500
<i>You break the rules, you die.</i>

52
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:11,780
<i>You follow them, you live.</i>

53
00:05:12,780 --> 00:05:13,900
<i>Maybe.</i>

54
00:05:34,380 --> 00:05:36,220
Hey. Look what I found.

55
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:39,620
Great.

56
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:43,780
Hey, if you happen to find a brand-new
factory-issued oil pan, holler.

57
00:05:49,460 --> 00:05:53,140
- Are you sure you can't fix it?
- It's blown, lvy Boy.

58
00:06:01,580 --> 00:06:03,340
- Brian.
- What?

59
00:06:06,460 --> 00:06:08,500
All that car needed was gas.

60
00:06:09,340 --> 00:06:12,660
Wait, what? No. No, no, no way.

61
00:06:13,420 --> 00:06:16,500
- Lf we sit here, we're just gonna die.
- We won't if we go back?

62
00:06:16,580 --> 00:06:19,860
You saw the girl.
You saw the blood, the rashes.

63
00:06:21,140 --> 00:06:22,900
Bobby, come on, you saw her.

64
00:06:22,940 --> 00:06:25,140
- Am I the only one here?
- Kate, we do not have a lot of options...

65
00:06:25,220 --> 00:06:26,420
They're your rules!

66
00:06:26,460 --> 00:06:28,540
Danny, tell your girlfriend
to get her shit together.

67
00:06:28,620 --> 00:06:31,700
- I'm not his girlfriend.
- She's not my girlfriend.

68
00:06:33,180 --> 00:06:36,700
All right, then tell me, tell me.
Why the hell is she here?

69
00:06:38,580 --> 00:06:40,860
Why didn't we let her sit tight
in her McMansion,

70
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:42,260
- waiting for the looters?
- Okay.

71
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:46,380
Could we just calm down and try
and think this thing through? Please.

72
00:06:47,380 --> 00:06:49,940
- Yeah.
- So what about the car?

73
00:06:52,220 --> 00:06:53,700
I don't know, Danny. I'm trying to think.

74
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:56,340
- Well, we need that car...
- I know that!

75
00:07:00,140 --> 00:07:01,180
Shit!

76
00:07:16,460 --> 00:07:18,860
All right, put your masks on, guys.

77
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:34,140
Frank Holloway.

78
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:39,860
We're gonna need your car.

79
00:07:43,020 --> 00:07:44,940
Yeah, I figured as much.

80
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:50,940
Do you really want to splatter
your brand-new vehicle

81
00:07:50,980 --> 00:07:55,220
with the insides of someone who,
for all you know, may be infected?

82
00:07:56,140 --> 00:07:57,980
We got loads of Clorox.

83
00:07:59,140 --> 00:08:01,020
- Cleanup is not my chief concern.
- Brian, that's all right.

84
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:03,260
- That's close enough.
- I picked up a radio transmission

85
00:08:03,340 --> 00:08:06,220
from a school outside of Farmington
last week.

86
00:08:06,460 --> 00:08:08,580
People from all over the state
are traveling there.

87
00:08:08,660 --> 00:08:09,860
For what?

88
00:08:10,260 --> 00:08:12,860
The CDC, they set up some kind
of emergency response center.

89
00:08:12,940 --> 00:08:14,820
They've got a new serum.

90
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:17,980
That's one hell of a story, man.
I don't think I've heard that one yet.

91
00:08:18,060 --> 00:08:19,140
Are they getting results?

92
00:08:19,220 --> 00:08:21,020
No, they're not getting any results, Kate.

93
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:24,980
They've got a new treatment, and I am
taking my daughter there in this car.

94
00:08:25,060 --> 00:08:28,140
Now, if you're onboard with that, great.
If not...

95
00:08:28,540 --> 00:08:31,060
This is a fairytale, and he knows it.

96
00:08:32,060 --> 00:08:33,620
It's the Baltimore vaccine all over again.

97
00:08:33,660 --> 00:08:35,220
It's a bunch of retrovirals
that don't work for shit.

98
00:08:35,300 --> 00:08:36,980
So go ahead, Brian.
Shoot him in the head.

99
00:08:37,060 --> 00:08:38,500
Wait! Hey.

100
00:08:42,060 --> 00:08:43,500
I got an idea.

101
00:09:10,580 --> 00:09:11,580
Hey.

102
00:09:12,780 --> 00:09:15,580
Want to know a secret? About boys?

103
00:09:16,940 --> 00:09:19,380
Their bark is worse than their bite.

104
00:09:19,740 --> 00:09:21,660
- You know what I mean?
- No.

105
00:09:21,740 --> 00:09:24,340
- It's okay.
- Don't listen to her, kiddo.

106
00:09:24,660 --> 00:09:28,540
- Trust me, she loves it when I bite.
- Why don't you eat me, Brian?

107
00:09:28,620 --> 00:09:32,420
- I think we can arrange that.
- Jesus, Brian! She's, like, eight.

108
00:09:32,860 --> 00:09:35,140
Yeah, well, mentally, so is he.

109
00:10:03,580 --> 00:10:07,060
<i>Adi√≥s, Road Warrior.
You crap piece of shit.</i>

110
00:10:10,940 --> 00:10:13,020
<i>But Godless governments have fallen,</i>

111
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:15,220
<i>and the armies of man
have perished by his hand...</i>

112
00:10:15,260 --> 00:10:16,620
Pattycake, pattycake...

113
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:21,620
<i>... for this pandemic is the flail of God
and the world his threshing floor,</i>

114
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:24,620
<i>and, implacably,
he will thresh out his harvest</i>

115
00:10:24,700 --> 00:10:29,060
<i>until the wheat is separated from
the chaff, the righteous from the sinner.</i>

116
00:10:29,340 --> 00:10:33,620
<i>And make no mistake about it,
there shall be far more chaff than wheat.</i>

117
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:35,420
<i>Few chosen...</i>

118
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:39,060
Come to think of it,
I haven't seen much weed around lately.

119
00:10:40,620 --> 00:10:43,260
- Very funny.
- What?

120
00:10:45,900 --> 00:10:47,740
Just show some respect.

121
00:10:47,780 --> 00:10:50,500
For what?
That God's punishing my daughter?

122
00:10:51,260 --> 00:10:53,620
Who's he rewarding? Who, you?

123
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:56,940
- That's not what I'm saying.
- What are you saying?

124
00:10:57,020 --> 00:10:59,060
Some people locked themselves away,
piled up food,

125
00:10:59,140 --> 00:11:02,300
didn't even pick up the phone.
They were dead in a week.

126
00:11:02,380 --> 00:11:04,340
Me, I worked at the stadium,
digging those mass graves for 400...

127
00:11:04,380 --> 00:11:06,980
- 400 bucks a day!
- That's exactly right.

128
00:11:07,460 --> 00:11:10,020
You can laugh all you want,
but I was up to my knees in that shit,

129
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:11,220
and here I am.

130
00:11:11,260 --> 00:11:14,740
So you're immune or chosen
or something?

131
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:17,420
I'm here and they're not.

132
00:11:18,620 --> 00:11:20,860
So, then, I guess you won't mind
kissing my daughter good night for me,

133
00:11:20,940 --> 00:11:22,260
huh, Brian?

134
00:11:24,420 --> 00:11:26,020
I didn't think so.

135
00:11:30,540 --> 00:11:32,660
So much for being chosen, huh?

136
00:11:33,780 --> 00:11:36,180
That's hysterical, huh, lvy League?

137
00:11:39,100 --> 00:11:40,700
Where'd you go to school, Danny?

138
00:11:40,780 --> 00:11:43,500
- He got a scholarship to go to Harvard.
- Yale.

139
00:11:43,580 --> 00:11:46,540
- It was Yale, actually.
- It doesn't really matter, does it?

140
00:11:46,620 --> 00:11:50,580
A little something shut the place down
before freshman orientation.

141
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:54,580
- Watch it, Brian.
- How's that for a knee-slapper?

142
00:11:55,060 --> 00:11:57,740
- Why do you have to be such a dick?
- Come on!

143
00:11:57,820 --> 00:11:59,540
Watch out! Watch out!

144
00:12:14,020 --> 00:12:16,020
You! You stay in the back, you hear me?

145
00:12:16,060 --> 00:12:18,740
Hey, I will if you keep your eyes
on the goddamn road!

146
00:12:18,780 --> 00:12:21,380
Hey, you can get out anytime!
You can get out right now!

147
00:12:21,460 --> 00:12:25,940
- Okay. Okay. Okay.
- Kate! Kate!

148
00:12:26,980 --> 00:12:29,940
The tape held.
You don't have to worry about it.

149
00:12:31,380 --> 00:12:34,580
Are you okay? What is it?

150
00:12:41,140 --> 00:12:43,860
Damn it.
I think she knocked a filling loose.

151
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:45,380
I weep for you.

152
00:12:50,220 --> 00:12:51,580
It's locked.

153
00:13:00,060 --> 00:13:01,660
Danny, be careful.

154
00:13:02,820 --> 00:13:04,100
It's okay.

155
00:13:14,020 --> 00:13:15,060
Shit.

156
00:13:31,540 --> 00:13:33,700
Hey, are you all right? Danny!

157
00:13:34,740 --> 00:13:35,860
What happened?

158
00:13:39,980 --> 00:13:41,100
Jesus!

159
00:13:42,220 --> 00:13:44,340
Just get the gas and let's go.

160
00:13:59,220 --> 00:14:01,900
Hey, kids, we'll be back in 20.

161
00:14:02,460 --> 00:14:05,020
Yeah, we'll be back in more like five.

162
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:07,340
Shit.

163
00:14:08,180 --> 00:14:10,100
Bobby! Baby?

164
00:14:11,220 --> 00:14:14,100
- What's that?
- That?

165
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:18,420
Well, Brian and I,

166
00:14:19,380 --> 00:14:22,620
we had a dad, too.
He was just like yours.

167
00:14:23,620 --> 00:14:27,620
And every summer, when we were little,
he would take us to this place.

168
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:29,300
It's Turtle Beach.

169
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:34,860
And we could swim and surf,
and we'd fish

170
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:39,740
<i>and eat these soft-shell crab
sandwiches that were soaked in mayo.</i>

171
00:14:43,220 --> 00:14:45,180
Were there lots of turtles?

172
00:14:45,260 --> 00:14:49,140
Lots? God, there were thousands
of them! They were everywhere.

173
00:14:49,580 --> 00:14:53,620
<i>I mean, you could barely put your foot
in the water without stepping on one.</i>

174
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:56,860
Sometimes they'd be stacked up
on top of each other.

175
00:14:57,060 --> 00:15:00,180
- That's impossible!
- It is possible.

176
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:04,900
- They were everywhere.
- Can we go to Turtle Beach with them?

177
00:15:06,260 --> 00:15:07,700
Time to sleep.

178
00:15:09,460 --> 00:15:12,420
What makes you think
you're gonna be safe there?

179
00:15:13,860 --> 00:15:15,540
It's an old motel.

180
00:15:16,460 --> 00:15:20,460
The place has been abandoned
for years. We'll go on scavenging trips

181
00:15:20,540 --> 00:15:23,860
and quarantine ourselves
every single time we get back,

182
00:15:24,260 --> 00:15:26,780
- and wait.
- Until they come for us.

183
00:15:27,860 --> 00:15:30,620
Until... Until the disease dies off.

184
00:15:31,740 --> 00:15:33,660
The disease or the people?

185
00:15:36,140 --> 00:15:38,180
It's the same thing, really.

186
00:15:41,260 --> 00:15:42,900
<i>Bobby, I love you,</i>

187
00:15:43,140 --> 00:15:46,180
and you know
what a dipshit I can be sometimes...

188
00:15:47,620 --> 00:15:49,300
What's the big deal?

189
00:15:52,260 --> 00:15:54,660
I think we should see other people.

190
00:15:57,980 --> 00:16:00,020
If that's the way you feel.

191
00:16:00,980 --> 00:16:02,700
It is the way I feel.

192
00:16:09,260 --> 00:16:12,140
- You can be such a dipshit sometimes.
- I know!

193
00:16:12,700 --> 00:16:15,700
Probably the biggest in the world
at this point.

194
00:16:36,740 --> 00:16:38,700
Do you ever think of Yale?

195
00:16:41,660 --> 00:16:43,540
Yeah. Sure.

196
00:16:45,580 --> 00:16:49,460
That, and all those things
you think you'll get to do someday.

197
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:57,220
Jesus!

198
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:01,220
- Put it out! Put the fire out!
- Go, go, go, go, go!

199
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:05,620
Where do you think you're going, boy?

200
00:17:05,980 --> 00:17:07,340
- Hurry up.
- Hurry.

201
00:17:07,420 --> 00:17:10,180
Just keep it down. Keep it down.
Put it out.

202
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:11,780
- Okay, I'll be right back.
- Daddy.

203
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:13,620
Honey, I'm just going in there

204
00:19:13,660 --> 00:19:15,260
to make sure
there are no monsters under the bed.

205
00:19:15,340 --> 00:19:17,940
If there are monsters, you shouldn't go.

206
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:21,540
Okay, now listen to me.
There's no reason to worry. All right?

207
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:23,220
I'll be back before you can say
Captain Feathersword.

208
00:19:23,300 --> 00:19:25,020
Captain Feathersword.

209
00:19:26,260 --> 00:19:28,300
You're too smart for me, you know that?

210
00:19:28,380 --> 00:19:30,020
I'll stay with her.

211
00:19:31,260 --> 00:19:32,340
Bobby.

212
00:19:33,020 --> 00:19:34,940
Look, now is not the time, okay?

213
00:19:34,980 --> 00:19:38,060
The girls need some alone time
to talk about boys.

214
00:19:42,140 --> 00:19:44,820
I am serious.
Do not get too close to her.

215
00:19:45,020 --> 00:19:49,260
I'm serious. Just go. It's gonna be fine.

216
00:19:52,340 --> 00:19:55,420
You know, you are always doing
whatever the hell you want.

217
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:57,340
That's why you love me!

218
00:20:14,660 --> 00:20:15,780
Hello?

219
00:20:19,580 --> 00:20:20,660
Hello?

220
00:20:57,340 --> 00:21:00,500
Looks like your hospital
ran out of patients, Frank.

221
00:21:04,020 --> 00:21:06,220
Come on. Let's get out of here.

222
00:21:10,940 --> 00:21:12,380
Where's Kate?

223
00:21:16,660 --> 00:21:18,580
- What is she doing?
- Kate?

224
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:22,020
- We have to go. There's nothing here.
- You don't know that.

225
00:21:22,100 --> 00:21:23,820
Kate, they failed. Let's go.

226
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:26,660
There's a whole wing
we haven't checked yet.

227
00:21:27,980 --> 00:21:30,180
You see? There are people here.

228
00:21:30,780 --> 00:21:31,860
Wait!

229
00:21:50,420 --> 00:21:51,740
No way.

230
00:21:53,180 --> 00:21:55,060
Oh, my God. They did it.

231
00:22:09,540 --> 00:22:12,180
- Sir. Sir!
- Yes?

232
00:22:14,700 --> 00:22:18,900
- Are you in charge here?
- No, you want Dr. Lindus.

233
00:22:19,220 --> 00:22:22,380
His office is on the second floor
of the old math building.

234
00:22:22,460 --> 00:22:25,500
But you won't find him there.
He died on Thursday.

235
00:22:26,780 --> 00:22:28,140
Doctor, we've come all the way
from Colorado.

236
00:22:28,220 --> 00:22:29,380
We heard that you had a serum here.

237
00:22:29,460 --> 00:22:33,060
It's my daughter, she's...
My daughter is very sick.

238
00:22:35,940 --> 00:22:38,180
- How long?
- A little over a week.

239
00:22:39,100 --> 00:22:41,740
- Is she bleeding from her ears yet?
- No.

240
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:46,380
Well, bring her in.

241
00:22:47,860 --> 00:22:51,700
Okay, kids, these nice people
are gonna take you to your parents,

