- That's not what I said.

484
00:52:21,380 --> 00:52:23,340
Brian, please let me stay.

485
00:52:26,180 --> 00:52:28,380
Brian, please don't!

486
00:52:29,900 --> 00:52:31,700
Brian, do not do this!

487
00:52:31,860 --> 00:52:34,540
- There's a town down that road.
- These are just bruises.

488
00:52:34,620 --> 00:52:36,020
I've been bouncing around
in the back of that

489
00:52:36,100 --> 00:52:37,980
- stupid car for days.
- I'm sure there's plenty of water in town,

490
00:52:38,060 --> 00:52:42,100
- but here's half a gallon.
- Of course I have bruises, but I am fine!

491
00:52:42,380 --> 00:52:44,660
- Lf you ration it...
- I love you.

492
00:52:45,180 --> 00:52:46,740
...it should last a few days.
- You love me, don't you?

493
00:52:46,820 --> 00:52:51,140
- The same goes for the food.
- Brian, I'll wear a mask. I didn't know.

494
00:52:51,220 --> 00:52:53,140
Like hell you didn't know!

495
00:52:54,100 --> 00:52:56,340
- I...
- Don't you do that!

496
00:52:56,940 --> 00:52:58,620
Don't you lie to me!

497
00:52:59,020 --> 00:53:00,460
I wasn't sure.

498
00:53:02,540 --> 00:53:06,860
Please don't leave me here!
Please, won't you help me?

499
00:53:14,860 --> 00:53:18,860
When you get to town,
you find a comfortable place,

500
00:53:18,940 --> 00:53:20,500
you know, with a good bed.

501
00:53:23,580 --> 00:53:26,620
And get yourself a blanket,
even if it feels hot now.

502
00:53:28,780 --> 00:53:30,380
And lots of water.

503
00:53:32,300 --> 00:53:34,420
Do it before you're too weak.

504
00:53:37,620 --> 00:53:39,780
Brian. Brian!

505
00:53:40,580 --> 00:53:42,620
I warned you about the girl.

506
00:53:43,580 --> 00:53:45,260
- You...
- I told you to stay away from her.

507
00:53:45,340 --> 00:53:48,180
Why the hell
couldn't you have listened to me?

508
00:53:50,340 --> 00:53:52,860
She was choking. She couldn't breathe.

509
00:54:29,820 --> 00:54:32,340
- Brian.
- Hey, hand me a beer, will you?

510
00:54:48,540 --> 00:54:49,780
Warm beer.

511
00:54:51,540 --> 00:54:53,100
Tastes like piss.

512
00:55:03,100 --> 00:55:04,980
- What are we gonna do?
- I don't know.

513
00:55:05,020 --> 00:55:07,220
- It's almost gone.
- I know that!

514
00:55:12,260 --> 00:55:13,260
Car.

515
00:55:14,300 --> 00:55:15,700
- I see it.
- We gotta make them stop.

516
00:55:15,740 --> 00:55:17,980
Yeah, we'll just wave politely
and ask for help.

517
00:55:18,060 --> 00:55:19,980
Brian. Brian!

518
00:55:34,100 --> 00:55:37,300
Hey! I'll deal with this.

519
00:55:44,380 --> 00:55:46,700
- Stay where you are!
- Don't come any closer!

520
00:55:46,780 --> 00:55:50,900
I'm gonna stay right here.
We just need some gas.

521
00:55:52,060 --> 00:55:56,820
- Sorry. We don't have any to spare.
- I know. I understand.

522
00:56:00,420 --> 00:56:03,340
But I was just hoping
that maybe as a fellow Christian,

523
00:56:03,420 --> 00:56:06,620
- you might be able to help us.
- Please don't do that.

524
00:56:07,700 --> 00:56:10,700
You see, my wife in the car,
she's pregnant.

525
00:56:11,580 --> 00:56:14,780
We're just looking for a cool place
to have the baby,

526
00:56:15,140 --> 00:56:18,740
- see this thing through.
- Go in reverse. Let's go. Let's go.

527
00:56:18,900 --> 00:56:20,180
Good luck.

528
00:56:20,820 --> 00:56:22,260
- Go, go, go.
- Ma'am.

529
00:56:22,340 --> 00:56:24,140
- No, I can't.
- Please.

530
00:56:24,220 --> 00:56:25,740
I'm begging you!

531
00:56:28,540 --> 00:56:29,780
No, Brian!

532
00:56:34,300 --> 00:56:35,460
Get out!

533
00:56:37,500 --> 00:56:38,700
Get out!

534
00:57:15,940 --> 00:57:17,300
Get the gas.

535
00:57:19,260 --> 00:57:20,300
Oh, God.

536
00:57:32,020 --> 00:57:33,620
What are you doing?

537
00:57:33,700 --> 00:57:36,340
They weren't gonna give it to us, Danny.

538
00:57:37,100 --> 00:57:38,500
Help her out.

539
00:57:41,740 --> 00:57:45,820
You don't talk to me. You hear me?
You don't tell me what to do!

540
00:57:47,060 --> 00:57:50,860
Don't walk away from me,
you son of a bitch! I'm talking to you!

541
00:57:51,660 --> 00:57:54,020
- What the...
- I am talking to you,

542
00:57:54,180 --> 00:57:57,580
and I'm telling you what to do,
you self-righteous shit!

543
00:57:58,020 --> 00:58:00,580
It must be nice sitting on the sidelines

544
00:58:00,660 --> 00:58:02,540
while your dumb brother
wades in shit for you.

545
00:58:02,620 --> 00:58:04,740
- No, I don't...
- Somebody had to do it.

546
00:58:04,820 --> 00:58:06,420
- Was it gonna be you, Danny?
- You didn't have to...

547
00:58:06,460 --> 00:58:09,060
You remember...
You remember our last day at home?

548
00:58:09,460 --> 00:58:12,860
It wasn't you who went up to Mom
and Dad's room to get his gun, was it?

549
00:58:12,940 --> 00:58:16,500
It wasn't you! It wasn't you
who had to go up there and lie

550
00:58:16,540 --> 00:58:19,980
and tell them not to worry,
that you'd be back real soon.

551
00:58:20,300 --> 00:58:23,540
- They were alive? Alive?
- You knew they were.

552
00:58:24,100 --> 00:58:27,700
They were? You... You told me...

553
00:58:27,740 --> 00:58:32,820
- What you wanted to hear.
- You asshole! Asshole!

554
00:58:35,300 --> 00:58:37,740
Come here. Come here.
I'm an asshole for what?

555
00:58:37,820 --> 00:58:39,380
Tell me, Danny, asshole for what?

556
00:58:39,460 --> 00:58:40,660
For what?

557
00:58:40,940 --> 00:58:43,900
For letting you walk by
with a clean conscience?

558
00:58:45,740 --> 00:58:48,060
Well, that's what you like, Danny.

559
00:58:49,980 --> 00:58:51,460
Remember Bobby?

560
00:58:53,820 --> 00:58:55,460
You remember Bobby?

561
00:58:56,060 --> 00:58:58,020
I was the one that had to drag her
out of the car

562
00:58:58,100 --> 00:59:01,420
while you just sat there
watching me do it!

563
00:59:09,660 --> 00:59:11,180
Bobby was right.

564
00:59:14,140 --> 00:59:15,940
You got all the brains.

565
01:00:49,820 --> 01:00:50,940
<i>Danny.</i>

566
01:00:58,340 --> 01:01:00,260
Hey. Brian.

567
01:01:05,220 --> 01:01:06,500
Stop here.

568
01:01:09,020 --> 01:01:10,540
Brian. Brian.

569
01:01:11,260 --> 01:01:12,340
We're gonna stop at this house, okay?

570
01:01:12,380 --> 01:01:15,540
We're gonna find something
to dress your wound with.

571
01:01:15,700 --> 01:01:17,460
Whatever you say, Doc.

572
01:01:45,860 --> 01:01:48,460
Danny. There.

573
01:01:58,460 --> 01:02:00,220
A little closer.

574
01:02:01,180 --> 01:02:03,020
Keep going. Okay, stop.

575
01:02:37,500 --> 01:02:38,620
Hello?

576
01:02:57,660 --> 01:02:58,740
Hello!

577
01:03:02,340 --> 01:03:05,420
If you can hear me,
we just need medical supplies.

578
01:03:09,060 --> 01:03:10,540
Someone's hurt.

579
01:03:15,100 --> 01:03:16,700
We're not infected,

580
01:03:19,100 --> 01:03:21,300
and we don't mean you any harm.

581
01:03:22,380 --> 01:03:23,540
We're...

582
01:03:24,540 --> 01:03:28,420
We're just gonna take what we need,
and we'll leave.

583
01:04:48,780 --> 01:04:51,460
What happened? Oh, shit!
What's on you?

584
01:04:58,100 --> 01:05:00,820
It's not contagious. It's not human blood.

585
01:05:03,340 --> 01:05:04,820
It's dog blood.

586
01:05:08,060 --> 01:05:11,020
- You had me worried, little brother.
- I'm sorry.

587
01:05:13,500 --> 01:05:14,460
Sorry.

588
01:05:20,140 --> 01:05:25,140
Hey, don't take this the wrong way.
Can you pull down your pants?

589
01:05:53,740 --> 01:05:56,420
Hey, so much for being chosen, huh?

590
01:06:01,020 --> 01:06:02,300
I'm sorry.

591
01:06:32,540 --> 01:06:34,420
He's got it, doesn't he?

592
01:06:40,060 --> 01:06:41,100
Shit!

593
01:06:45,860 --> 01:06:49,460
<i>I don't know if there's anybody listening,</i>

594
01:06:50,700 --> 01:06:52,860
<i>but my generator is dying.</i>

595
01:06:53,780 --> 01:06:58,140
<i>So, if there is someone out there,
this is my last song.</i>

596
01:06:59,140 --> 01:07:02,980
<i>This is Laura Merkin,
last survivor of Corpus Christi, Texas,</i>

597
01:07:03,620 --> 01:07:05,780
<i>saying goodbye.</i>

598
01:07:21,340 --> 01:07:22,860
Can I see those?

599
01:07:46,820 --> 01:07:50,460
Bobby had this crazy idea.

600
01:07:53,660 --> 01:07:55,460
She wanted to be a mom.

601
01:07:59,620 --> 01:08:01,340
Can you believe that?

602
01:08:03,420 --> 01:08:04,620
Why not?

603
01:08:07,140 --> 01:08:08,340
With me?

604
01:08:12,220 --> 01:08:15,180
There are some things
I'm just not good at, man.

605
01:08:18,940 --> 01:08:20,620
Where did she get...

606
01:08:22,780 --> 01:08:23,900
A baby?

607
01:08:30,860 --> 01:08:33,740
Who knows?
Maybe I would have been good at it.

608
01:09:36,820 --> 01:09:38,420
Hey, Danny. Danny?

609
01:09:41,460 --> 01:09:44,660
I gotta tell you something. It's a secret.

610
01:09:46,420 --> 01:09:48,340
You want to hear a secret?

611
01:09:50,900 --> 01:09:52,740
- Sure.
- At the stadium,

612
01:09:57,940 --> 01:10:00,260
some of those people, they were...

613
01:10:02,500 --> 01:10:04,620
They were still alive, Danny.

614
01:10:07,220 --> 01:10:10,180
We were gonna dump them in the grave
and then...

615
01:10:11,700 --> 01:10:13,620
Some of them would move.

616
01:10:16,380 --> 01:10:18,340
I'd look at the supervisor,

617
01:10:20,260 --> 01:10:22,300
and he'd pretend not to see, so...

618
01:10:24,820 --> 01:10:27,060
So we'd pretend not to see them,

619
01:10:29,340 --> 01:10:30,620
but we did.

620
01:10:32,260 --> 01:10:34,580
We did, and we'd bury them anyway.

621
01:10:36,180 --> 01:10:39,300
- There were so many bodies, Danny.
- I know.

622
01:10:40,100 --> 01:10:42,260
- So many.
- I know.

623
01:10:45,180 --> 01:10:47,300
How the hell did we get here?

624
01:10:50,740 --> 01:10:54,100
- I don't know, Brian.
- You know.

625
01:10:56,660 --> 01:10:58,100
We both know.

626
01:10:59,980 --> 01:11:01,380
We both know.

627
01:11:03,900 --> 01:11:05,300
We both know.

628
01:11:06,900 --> 01:11:08,700
We both...

629
01:11:49,340 --> 01:11:51,180
Where you going, Danny?

630
01:11:57,660 --> 01:11:59,380
Where you going, man?

631
01:12:00,540 --> 01:12:02,260
We're leaving, Brian.

632
01:12:13,780 --> 01:12:16,620
- Come on.
- Come on, come on, come on, come on!

633
01:12:20,100 --> 01:12:22,700
- Shit!
- Oh, my God.

634
01:12:58,180 --> 01:13:00,100
I need those keys, Brian.

635
01:13:01,140 --> 01:13:02,180
Sure.

636
01:13:04,340 --> 01:13:05,940
And I need a ride.

637
01:13:08,500 --> 01:13:11,420
- You know I can't.
- Come on, Danny.

638
01:13:13,740 --> 01:13:17,620
The ocean, you and me, one more time.

639
01:13:19,420 --> 01:13:21,300
You remember how it was.

640
01:13:22,620 --> 01:13:26,060
Hitting those waves
before everything turned to shit.

641
01:13:27,540 --> 01:13:29,340
Just give me the keys.

642
01:13:31,100 --> 01:13:32,540
You want them?

643
01:13:33,660 --> 01:13:37,340
Shoot me or take me with you.

644
01:13:40,940 --> 01:13:44,660
- Brian, don't do it.
- I'm not gonna end up like them, Danny.

645
01:13:47,020 --> 01:13:49,300
Rotting alive, alone.

646
01:13:51,180 --> 01:13:53,860
You can't tell whether they're alive
or dead.

647
01:13:53,940 --> 01:13:56,300
Please, Brian. Don't.

648
01:13:59,580 --> 01:14:02,220
- It's what we decided.
- I'm dying, Danny!

649
01:14:05,220 --> 01:14:07,660
I don't give a fuck about the rules.

650
01:14:11,260 --> 01:14:12,700
You made them.

651
01:14:15,140 --> 01:14:16,740
My little brother.

652
01:14:18,780 --> 01:14:21,100
I taught him everything he knows.

653
01:15:14,540 --> 01:15:18,340
<i>I drive and wait for a storm to come</i>

654
01:15:20,020 --> 01:15:21,740
<i>and wash us all away,</i>

655
01:15:23,780 --> 01:15:25,260
<i>but it doesn't.</i>

656
01:15:30,420 --> 01:15:32,140
<i>It's a beautiful day.</i>

657
01:15:33,780 --> 01:15:36,180
<i>And it shouldn't be a beautiful day.</i>

658
01:15:39,500 --> 01:15:40,660
<i>I wait,</i>

659
01:15:43,100 --> 01:15:45,060
<i>but nothing happens to me.</i>

660
01:15:48,500 --> 01:15:53,180
<i>And for the first time,
I feel like I am alone in the world.</i>

661
01:16:08,020 --> 01:16:12,020
<i>We made it.
Two strangers with nothing left to say.</i>

662
01:16:17,300 --> 01:16:19,740
<i>Brian and I used to love this place,</i>

663
01:16:21,060 --> 01:16:23,380
<i>the hotel, the beach.</i>

664
01:16:28,020 --> 01:16:32,700
<i>They still look exactly the same,
but they're just places now.</i>

665
01:16:43,580 --> 01:16:45,580
<i>Brian! Danny! Come on!</i>

666
01:16:45,620 --> 01:16:47,940
<i>I don't know what'll happen next.</i>

667
01:16:48,980 --> 01:16:51,220
<i>I don't know how long I'll live.</i>

668
01:17:00,420 --> 01:17:02,420
<i>But I know I will be alone.</i>

